&quot;Mages way to dominant mid&quot; meanwhile I play against assassins literally fucking 80% of my games.

I dont give a flying fuck if assassins dont get picked in LCS, they are literally EVERYWHERE in soloq.



Edit- Highlighting Teridax68's post for relevance. 

**T**eridax68 (NA)  - 
To add some stats to what the OP is saying, using op.gg:

Fizz has a 51.65% win rate and a 7.45% play rate. He therefore has good presence mid and good success as well.
Zed has a 50.63% win rate and a 10.35% play rate. He therefore has a very large presence mid, along with good success there.
LeBlanc has a 46.78% win rate and a 15.67% play rate. Her win rate isn't amazing, but she is literally the most popular mid laner in the game.
Katarina has a 52.4% win rate and a 4.78% play rate. She's not as popular as the others (though still not bad by any means), but is among the more successful mid lane champions.
Kassadin has a 49.17% win rate and a 8.74% play rate. He therefore has good presence mid, as well as reasonably good success.
Yasuo has a 50.19% win rate and a 11.18% play rate. He therefore has a very large presence mid, as well as good success.
So effectively, outside of pro play, assassins are already both highly present and successful in mid lane. Assassins are among the top-performing mid lane champions, with 5 out of the top 10 mid laners, and 2 out of the top 4, being assassins. The same applies when ranking in terms of popularity, and 6 out of the 10 most-banned mid laners are assassins. Meanwhile, iconic mid lane mages like Lux, Syndra, Vel'Koz, Viktor, Xerath and Ziggs all have play rates under 4% (many of these champions in fact have play rates barely above 1%), along with win rates under 50%. With these mana changes, Riot is therefore setting out to unbalance the game for practically the entirety of League's playerbase, purely to address a problem that affects a tiny subset of players, and so in a manner that is unlikely to even resolve the actual issue. It's a terrible idea that is going to generate negative feedback for months, if not years on end, depending on how quickly it gets addressed, and the solution here should be to make changes that specifically target pro play, instead of screwing over literal thousands, if not millions of other players.****

replies.body:
I think it's probably because those champions have higher mechanical skill caps, a huge number of counter's and fall off(usually, looking at you Yasuo, with yourr 0/9 powerspike.). 

Like, for example if your the Sup and you see an Evelynn on the enemy team, pick Morgana(Though i ban her.) reason? She hard counter's Evelynn W, which is core to her kit and basically 30% of her reason she can one shot somebody, all morgana has to do is Spellshield somebody when Eve W's them and she can't kill them. 

Kasssadin and Yasuo are "Late-Game" scaling Assassin/Fighter's, both of them can one shot you if their ahead and Kassadin has some amazing one shot's later into the game but there are plenty of counter's for both of them, and remember both of them have horrific lane phases. Basically you want to pick someone that can either, shut them down early(Such as Malzahar or other Assassins that have better early games) or you'll pick someone who has a safe lane phase, good wave management and outscales them anyway. 

Counter's for Late Game Assassins: {{champion:13}} {{champion:69}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:43}} {{champion:40}} {{champion:16}} and all Early Game Assassins. 

Fizz, Zed and Katarina are Mid-Game assassins, their spike usually happens during Lane Phase and Continues into Mid-Game where they more often than not get fed due to lack of play around them. Unlike Kassadin and Yasuo, the actually have pretty strong early games but they fall off really hard late, so anyone that can lose lane and win the game, such as Yasuo or Kassadin are good same class counter's going into them but early game focused champions that are good at Roaming are really great to since you don't have to worry about their early game power at all and will scale better later anyway. 

Counter's for Mid-Game Assassins: {{champion:3}} (Match their Roams) {{champion:91}} (Your early game is stronger than all 3 of those champions.) {{champion:31}} (It's saucy but it works, silence+CC+true damage execute, they can't do anything.) {{champion:43}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:37}} 

You'll notice something, in both versions i listed Enchanter supports, the reason why is because they completely negate an Assassins damage if the assassin isn't already fed. Assassins unlike other classes rely heavily on getting ahead and staying ahead, to prevent them from doing that pick champions that farm well, scale well, out trade them or are just too tanky for them to deal with but these rules extend past Mid-Lane options. Chances are if you pick any of these champions. 

{{champion:99}} {{champion:134}} {{champion:61}} {{champion:142}} 

You'll probably end up against an assassin, and while you can take Exhaust, Barrier or Heal to prevent them from killing you easily your team needs to pick something to stop them in Mid-Game and Late-Game. If your team is full of squishies and has 0 CC or Healing, the assassin has a field day. So if you have the option and you pick after the assassin does, pick a counter to them if one doesn't already exist, trust me it'll make their life a living hell because you have just 1 counter. 

Honorable Mentions: {{champion:89}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:25}} {{champion:9}}
